   {:e #blake3 "c791e76edb5395b8943750084c1bbe94047f2e92bec3b4223e454201f8d12061" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-bd22f391; Session entity: :task/t-849613d4; REVISED IMPLEMENTATION ORDER (falsification-first applied to the plan itself). The formalism says seek falsification first. So we should falsify the formalism first. PHASE 0: EXTERNAL TEST — deploy braid as-is on a non-braid project BEFORE implementing the formalism. Record what breaks. This is the ultimate falsification of C8 substrate independence. PHASE 1: MINIMUM VIABLE FORMALISM (~150 LOC) — DC-1 (comonadic schema) + DC-2 (depth-weighted F(S)) + DC-4 (braid challenge) + CACHE-BUG fix. PHASE 2: MEASURE — HL-1..4 (hypothesis ledger, record predictions vs outcomes). PHASE 3: DIAGNOSE — DC-8 (diagnostic map: divergence type x triangle vertex -> prescribed fix). PHASE 4: EVERYTHING ELSE — remaining tasks, gated by whether Phase 1-3 validate the theory. Key principle: the depth weights (0.0, 0.15, 0.4, 0.7, 1.0) are a PRIOR, not truth — they should be treated as hypotheses at depth 1 and calibrated empirically. The plan itself is a hypothesis that should be falsified before full commitment.; FRACTAL SELF-APPLICATION + LEARNED SAW-TOOTH. The hypothetico-deductive loop applies at EVERY level of abstraction, forming a fractal tower: Level 0 (Reality): observe artifacts via extractors, reconcile boundary coverage, project code/tests/docs. Level 1 (Predictions): observe hypothesis outcomes, reconcile calibration error, project adjusted weights. Level 2 (Learning Rate): observe surprise trajectory, reconcile saw-tooth health, project expected surprise rate. Level 3 (Meta-Learning): observe calibration accuracy, reconcile meta-stability, project learning rate parameters. Each level is the SAME three operations (assert, falsify, witness) applied to the output of the level below. The saw-tooth healthy surprise rate IS a learned projection — it starts as a policy parameter (10-20%) and converges to the empirical rate through OBSERVER-4 applied at the meta-level. When actual surprise rate diverges from expected, that's a meta-divergence, diagnosed the same way as Level 0 divergence. The system learns its own learning dynamics. Echo-chamber detection: Level 2 diagnosis of assertion staleness at Level 0.; Session entity: :recon/trace-4ba31728c7758ae2; Session entity: :recon/trace-cf83093a3f3d531f; THE DIAGNOSTIC MAP (ADR-FOUNDATION-022). Each of the 8 divergence types maps to a SPECIFIC failure mode in the epistemological triangle. This makes the formalism DIAGNOSTIC, not just structural. Mapping: EPISTEMIC=assertion gap (observer didn't fire, fix: harvest), STRUCTURAL=adjunction gap (observe(project(store))\\!=store, fix: implement or re-spec), CONSEQUENTIAL=witness weakness (evidence doesn't hold, fix: deepen witness), ALEATORY=assertion conflict (observers disagree, fix: CRDT merge), LOGICAL=self-falsification (store contradicts itself, fix: comonadic challenge), AXIOLOGICAL=meta-assertion gap (goals not captured, fix: assert goals explicitly), TEMPORAL=assertion ordering (observations not merged, fix: sync barrier), PROCEDURAL=projection ineffectiveness (methodology ignored, fix: re-project AGENTS.md). Implementation: diagnose(store, delta) -> Vec<Diagnosis> where Diagnosis = {divergence_type, triangle_vertex, boundary, delta_fs, specific_gap, prescribed_fix: String (braid command), meta_level: 0-3}. Transforms braid status from dashboard into diagnostic instrument. Every F(S) drop has a classified cause and executable fix. ~200 LOC in bilateral.rs + status.rs.; Session entity: :task/t-b1eb3bf6; Session entity: :task/t-35a3e8bf" :op :assert}
